\begin_layout Paragraph
I programmed two times the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Dekker Algorithm
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 with different results.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subparagraph
In the first the time, I just added the a new class, with its respective
 object thread, slightly modifying the conditions to in the previous classes,
 to accept the concurrency, and work together.
 In the end, I only obtained a small glimpse of concurrency, due to appearance
 of deadlocks and infinite waitings between threads.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subparagraph
In the second time, I forced the turn incrementation and changed the wait
 condition in every 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

thread
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 class, making possible to run the code during a undefined number of iterations
 without any block, and being able to acces de critical region once per
 turn.
\end_layout

